The paper focuses on improving answer selection in information retrieval systems using pre-trained word embeddings, which is a common task in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of machine learning techniques such as learning-to-rank (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.AI) is also mentioned. Finally, the paper discusses the empirical results of experiments conducted on publicly available datasets (cs.CC).
